      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:1:39:14",
      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/39/737",
      "text": [
        " «إِذَا جُفِّفَتْ فَلاَ بَأْسَ بِالصَّلاَةِ عَلَيْهَا."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.737 - Ammar ibn Musa al-Sabati asked Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) about a mat made of reeds that had been wetted with impure water, and whether it is permissible to pray on it.\nImam (as) said: \"If it has dried, then there is no harm in praying on it”."
        ]
      }
